WandB

from fastai2.callback.tracker import SaveModelCallback
{% endraw %}

What is Weights and Biases?

Weights and Biases (usually called W&B or WandB) is a company, library and service that lets you share and log your results in a profile managed site. Their focus revolves around tracking, improving and sharing models.

The difference between WandB and TensorBoard is what problem they try to solve. TensorBoard is mostly used to visualize your data, including hyperparameters and model structure. WandB, on they other hand, tackles the problem with reproducability, using version control to allow us to point a run to a specific version of our code, making reproducability much simpler

Because of this, these tools are not exclusive, which means that you can upload your TensorBoard to your WandB run. This way, you can have your TensorBoard referenced to each one of your significan versions, allowing for compairisons even after making large changes.

Training

{% raw %} 
def group_callbacks(path:Path, board:bool, save:bool):
    cbs = [WandbCallback()]
    if board: cbs.append(TensorBoardCallback(log_dir=path))
    if save: cbs.append(SaveModelCallback(fname=path.name, every_epoch=True, with_opt=True))
    return Tuple(cbs)

def train_with(epochs:int=4, path:Path=tboard_path, board:bool=False, save:bool=False):
    cbs = group_callbacks(path,board,save)
    learner = Learner(dls, resnet34(pretrained=True), metrics=error_rate)
    learner.fit_one_cycle(4, cbs=callbacks)
    learner.show_results()
    torch.cuda.empty_cache()
